that’s generated. I wonder if the method `Class.forName` is involved, and maybe the agent registers itself in this process? There’s a lot to untangle here, and I want to ensure everything is working as it should!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering method handles and reflection**\\n\\nI’m thinking about using `String.class.getName()` to bypass reflection metadata, as it returns the JDK class. It seems fine because existing tests like AuthFilter pass. However, I need to explore if `MethodHandles.privateLookupIn` requires metadata. For native methods, I’m wondering if accessing a private static method might involve reflection. An agent should handle that. I could also use `getDeclaredMethod` directly, but it looks like existing approaches already utilize `MethodHandles`. I need to create a file for this.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_jijMKWaV59ursKuqAFc8B0ZM|fc_09d12e431a736d38016a27e6e163288194b6d696c494b8b026", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.rest-assured/rest-assured/5.5.0/src/test/java/io_rest_assured/rest_assured/RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelperInner_createClosureThatCalls_closure2Test.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_rest_assured.rest_assured;\n\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandle;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodHandles;\nimport java.lang.invoke.MethodType;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicReference;\n\nimport groovy.lang.Closure;\nimport io.restassured.internal.RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelper;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelperInner_createClosureThatCalls_closure2Test {\n    @Test\n    void wrapperClosureDelegatesResponseAndContentToAssertionClosure() throws Throwable {\n        Object response = new Object();\n        Object content = \"response content\";\n        AtomicReference<Object> capturedResponse = new AtomicReference<>();\n        AtomicReference<Object> capturedContent = new AtomicReference<>();\n        Closure<String> assertionClosure = new Closure<>(this) {\n            public String doCall(Object actualResponse, Object actualContent) {\n                capturedResponse.set(actualResponse);\n                capturedContent.set(actualContent);\n                return \"assertion result\";\n            }\n        };\n\n        Closure<?> wrapperClosure = RestAssuredHttpBuilderGroovyHelper.createClosureThatCalls(assertionClosure);\n\n        Object result = wrapperClosure.call(response, content);\n        Class<?> resolvedClass = invokeGeneratedClassLookup(wrapperClosure, String.class.getName());\n\n        assertThat(result).isEqualTo(\"assertion result\");\n        assertThat(capturedResponse).hasValue(response);\n        assertThat(capturedContent).hasValue(content);\n        assertThat(resolvedClass).isEqualTo(String.class);\n    }\n\n    private static Class<?> invokeGeneratedClassLookup(Closure<?> closure, String className) throws Throwable {\n        Class<?> closureClass = closure.getClass();\n        MethodHandles.Lookup lookup = MethodHandles.privateLookupIn(closureClass, MethodHandles.lookup());\n        MethodHandle classHelper = lookup.findStatic(\n                closureClass,\n                \"class$\",\n                MethodType.methodType(Class.class, String.class));\n        return (Class<?>) classHelper.invoke(className);\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1362, "output": 1710, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33792, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780999873386, "responseId": "resp_09d12e431a736d38016a27e6c1ebb88194bde465f9a3bdca95"}, "